claim.claim-text:
1. A process of providing a semiconductor device with electrical interconnection capability comprising the steps of: 
(a) depositing an electrically conductive seed layer on a semiconductor device provided with topographical features; 
(b) depositing a sacrificial material, said sacrificial material soluble in liquid or supercritical carbon dioxide, on said semiconductor device; 
(c) polishing said surface of said semiconductor device with a chemical mechanical polish wherein said seed layer and said sacrificial material is removed from all but the topographical features of said semiconductor device; and 
(d) contacting said semiconductor device with liquid or supercritical carbon dioxide wherein said sacrificial material is removed from said topographical features of said semiconductor device.
